---
By: Heraclitus
Source:
  ID: 996c9a12-d13d-4597-a783-506d70cd1736
  Locus:
    Verse: 15
---
For if it were not to Dionysus that they made a procession and sang the
shameful phallic hymn, they would be acting most shamelessly. But Hades
is the same as Dionysus in whose honor they go mad and rave.
